ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: It's a good chance to practice presentation skills.Yes. Because it's required.
Its a required course, this question is not relevant.

GSS is essentially a journal club, with the added benefit of getting feedback on your presentations. It allows you to get to know other professors in the apartment, which is useful. It's a required course, so I would recommend taking it if one wants to stay in the genetics department.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: The course helps me touch upon several aspects of my discipline.It helps me with my qualifying exam.
Gives insight into academia and various areas of genetics.
This course helped develop critical reading skills, and to a lesser degree, presentation skills.

I'm not sure if this course contributed to my research, save to hone my presentation skills. But it is always nice to read on other topics. This course gives you some introduction to what other professors/labs work on here at Yale.
